  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Let <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>H</mi></math> be a Riemannian homogeneous space. For an orthogonal representation ϕ of H on the Euclidean space <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> , there corresponds the vector bundle <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>G</mi><msub><mrow><mo>×</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>ϕ</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">→</mo><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>H</mi></math> with fiberwise inner product. Provided that ϕ is the direct sum of at most two representations which are either trivial or irreducible, we construct metrics of constant scalar curvature on the unit sphere bundle UE of E . When <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>H</mi></math> is the round sphere, we study the number of constant scalar curvature metrics in the conformal classes of these metrics.</subfield>
